# Geography Quiz — environment configuration (Vite).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) to override values locally:
#     cp .env.example .env.local
#
# Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to client code, and they are
# BAKED IN AT BUILD TIME (changing one requires a rebuild). Vite loads `.env`,
# `.env.local`, `.env.<mode>` etc. automatically.

# --- Backend (Phase 50 — optional, additive) -----------------------------------
# Base URL of the PocketBase backend. The app is offline-first and fully
# functional with this UNSET — the backend only *adds* capabilities when present.
#
#   • Unset  → in `dev` the app falls back to http://localhost:8090 (so
#              ./server/run.sh "just works"); in a production build it means the
#              backend is OFF and the app behaves exactly as it does today.
#   • Set    → the app probes this URL's health endpoint in the background and
#              shows the result in Settings → About.
#
# Must be HTTPS in production (the PWA is served over HTTPS, so a plain-http
# backend would be blocked as mixed content). See server/README.md.
#
# VITE_PB_URL=http://localhost:8090
